- He is focused on achieving his goal regardless of the consequences.
- He prioritizes the success of his mission over the well-being of individuals.
- He believes that the end justifies the means.
- He subscribes to the philosophy that the greater good is more important than individual suffering.
- He is willing to sacrifice a few for the benefit of many.
- He views the suffering of innocents as collateral damage in pursuit of a larger objective.
- He is indifferent to the suffering of others if it means achieving his aims.
- He is driven by a utilitarian perspective that values the outcome over the process.